@startuml
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-INSPECT)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-DIALECT)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-PURPOSE)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-ACCESS-CHECK)
'
' Objective-side use cases for the /mdd-deploy utility skill. STANDALONE,
' a sibling of /mdd-render: NOT wired into /mdd-cycle, /mdd-map,
' /mdd-validate, or /mdd-review; never executes a deploy command.
'
' CHANGE (cycle 0016): /mdd-deploy is made ADAPTIVE to the class of
' ambiguity that produced the Key Vault provisioning failure and the
' dev-vs-prod DB-SKU mismatch. Two new operator-facing gates join the
' dialect gate, and the existing landmine pause is GENERALIZED:
'   - USE-DEPLOY-PURPOSE: confirm the deployment purpose (dev/staging/
'     prod) BEFORE any purpose-driven default (DB tier, redundancy, the
'     recommended network/doorway posture). No silent default; the skill
'     SURFACES purpose-appropriate options for the operator to confirm.
'   - USE-DEPLOY-ACCESS-CHECK: before emitting, account for who READS and
'     who WRITES every secured store, each with an identity and a network
'     path the chosen posture actually admits; a store read-but-never-
'     written, or a writer with no admitted path, is SURFACED as a
'     blocking question rather than shipped as a complete-looking diagram.
' Both gates SURFACE the choice; they never bake in an answer (no default
' allowlist, no default DB tier). The skill still executes nothing.
'
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE, "Operator runs /mdd-deploy with a one-line deployment description; the skill produces a UML deployment diagram, secure-by-default generated IaC in the CONFIRMED dialect, and an explicit runbook that preserves the target's security invariants. It pauses with a BLOCKING clarification on ambiguity and on any GENERALIZED landmine — any choice whose correctness depends on a fact not grounded in the inputs it read (now covering the access-path axis: who reaches a secured store; and the purpose axis: dev vs prod — not just the original app-config axis). It SURFACES such gaps and hardened-default trade-offs for the operator to decide instead of jumping to a solution. The skill executes nothing — the human runs the commands.")
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-INSPECT, "Operator inspects the generated deployment diagram visually: /mdd-render also rasterizes .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml to .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg. Additive and non-gating.")
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-DIALECT, "Before any deploy artifact is created, /mdd-deploy resolves the requested IaC dialect (Bicep or Terraform), presents it back, and BLOCKS for an explicit operator confirmation. No silent default; exactly one dialect per run; Terraform enforces the same invariants + secure-by-default posture as Bicep, differing only in structure (main.tf + modules + azurerm provider + remote state backend).")
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-PURPOSE, "Before any purpose-driven default is generated, /mdd-deploy establishes the deployment purpose — dev, staging, or prod — and BLOCKS for explicit operator confirmation, the same discipline as the dialect gate. No silent default: the skill never assumes prod-grade or dev-grade. The confirmed purpose then drives the defaults that hang on it — Azure DB for PostgreSQL tier/redundancy, backup retention, and which network/doorway posture is RECOMMENDED — but the skill surfaces purpose-appropriate options for the operator to confirm; the vault stays most-restrictive by default and any relaxation remains an explicit, surfaced decision (secure-by-default is preserved, not overridden).")
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-ACCESS-CHECK, "Before writing the deployment diagram and IaC, /mdd-deploy runs an access-completeness pass over every secured store (Key Vault, the database, the registry, remote state): for each it must name who READS it and who WRITES/provisions it, each with an identity and a network path the chosen posture actually admits. A store that is read but never written (e.g. secrets nobody is shown provisioning), or a writer with no admitted path through a door the skill just locked, is a hole the skill SURFACES as a BLOCKING question — it never ships a diagram that only looks complete. It surfaces the connectivity options (e.g. allowlist / in-VNet / tunnel) framed by the deployment purpose; the operator chooses.")
title /mdd-deploy deployment guidance — use cases (objective)

left to right direction

actor "Operator" as Op

rectangle "mdd toolchain (utility, outside the parity gate)" {
  usecase "Guide an Azure Container Apps\ndeployment via a diagram,\nrunbook, and generated IaC" as Guide
  usecase "Choose & CONFIRM the IaC dialect\n(Bicep XOR Terraform) before any\nartifact is written — no silent default" as Dialect
  usecase "Confirm the deployment PURPOSE\n(dev/staging/prod) before any\npurpose-driven default — no silent default" as Purpose
  usecase "Account for who READS and WRITES\nevery secured store (identity + admitted\npath) before emitting — surface holes" as AccessCheck
  usecase "Inspect the generated\ndeployment diagram as SVG" as Inspect
}

Op --> Guide
Op --> Dialect
Op --> Purpose
Op --> AccessCheck
Op --> Inspect

Guide ..> Dialect : <<include>>
Guide ..> Purpose : <<include>>
Guide ..> AccessCheck : <<include>>
Guide ..> Inspect : <<extend>>

note bottom of Guide
  v1 target: azure-container-apps (../atlas-ate-server).
  Reads .mdd/models + the target repo READ-ONLY.
  PAUSES with a BLOCKING clarification on ambiguity OR
  a GENERALIZED go-live landmine — any choice whose
  correctness depends on a fact NOT grounded in the
  inputs (access-path axis + purpose axis, not just
  app-config). Surfaces the gap/trade-off instead of
  jumping to a solution; never a buried runbook STOP
  note. Writes diagram + runbook + SECURE-BY-DEFAULT
  IaC in the confirmed dialect, then STOPS. NEVER runs
  az / docker / terraform / brew.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE.
end note

note bottom of Dialect
  Mandatory <<include>>: guidance cannot proceed until
  the dialect is explicitly confirmed. One per run
  (Bicep XOR Terraform). FULL PARITY — both enforce the
  identical invariant checklist + secure-by-default
  posture; only IaC structure differs.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE.
end note

note bottom of Purpose
  Mandatory <<include>>: no purpose-driven default
  (DB tier/redundancy, backup retention, recommended
  doorway) is generated until dev/staging/prod is
  confirmed. No silent default; the skill never assumes
  prod- or dev-grade. Purpose RECOMMENDS; the operator
  confirms. Secure-by-default is preserved — the vault
  stays most-restrictive and any relaxation is explicit.
  Constrained by OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-PURPOSE /
  OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-SURFACE-NOT-DECIDE.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE.
end note

note bottom of AccessCheck
  Mandatory <<include>>: before emitting, every secured
  store must have a named READER and WRITER, each with
  an identity and a network path the posture admits.
  A read-but-never-written store, or a writer with no
  admitted path, is SURFACED as a blocking question —
  not shipped as a complete-looking diagram. Surfaces
  the connectivity options framed by purpose; operator
  chooses. Constrained by OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-ACCESS-COMPLETE
  / OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-SURFACE-NOT-DECIDE.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE.
end note

note bottom of Inspect
  Not a gate. /mdd-validate, /mdd-review and the
  /mdd-cycle parity loop never read .mdd/deploy/.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-INSPECT.
end note
@enduml
